## Architecture Overview

The backend follows a **layered DDD architecture** adapted for AWS Lambda:

```
src/
├── domain/           # Business logic, entities, value objects, repository interfaces
├── application/      # Use cases, services, validators — orchestrates domain
├── infrastructure/   # DynamoDB repositories, external adapters, AWS SDK clients
└── presentation/     # Lambda handlers — thin entry points, delegate to application layer
```

**Dependency rule**: outer layers depend on inner layers. Domain has zero dependencies on infrastructure or AWS SDK.

```
presentation → application → domain ← infrastructure
```

