## Validation

Validators live in `src/application/validators/`. They receive `unknown` input and return a typed, validated object — or throw `ValidationError`.

```typescript
// src/application/validators/fooValidator.ts
import { ValidationError } from '../../infrastructure/errors/ValidationError';

export interface CreateFooInput {
  name: string;
}

export function validateCreateFoo(input: unknown): CreateFooInput {
  if (typeof input !== 'object' || input === null) {
    throw new ValidationError('Request body must be a JSON object');
  }

  const body = input as Record<string, unknown>;

  if (typeof body.name !== 'string' || body.name.trim().length === 0) {
    throw new ValidationError('name is required and must be a non-empty string');
  }

  return { name: body.name.trim() };
}
```

**Rules:**
- Validate at the application layer boundary (before domain)
- Return typed objects from validators, never `any`
- Throw `ValidationError` with descriptive messages
- Do not use external validation libraries unless strictly necessary

