## Testing Standards

### Coverage Threshold

Minimum 90% for branches, functions, lines, and statements.

### Structure

```
__tests__/
├── unit/
│   ├── domain/
│   ├── application/
│   └── infrastructure/
└── integration/     # Optional: tests against DynamoDB Local
```

### Unit Test Pattern

Follow **AAA (Arrange, Act, Assert)**. Mock all infrastructure dependencies.

```typescript
// __tests__/unit/application/fooService.test.ts
import { createFoo } from '../../../src/application/services/fooService';
import { IFooRepository } from '../../../src/domain/repositories/IFooRepository';

const mockRepository: jest.Mocked<IFooRepository> = {
  save: jest.fn(),
  findById: jest.fn(),
  findAll: jest.fn(),
};

jest.mock('../../../src/infrastructure/dynamodb/FooRepository', () => ({
  FooRepository: jest.fn().mockImplementation(() => mockRepository),
}));

describe('createFoo', () => {
  beforeEach(() => jest.clearAllMocks());

  it('saves a new Foo and returns its id', async () => {
    // Arrange
    mockRepository.save.mockResolvedValue(undefined);

    // Act
    const result = await createFoo({ name: 'Test' });

    // Assert
    expect(result.id).toBeDefined();
    expect(mockRepository.save).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });

  it('throws ValidationError when name is missing', async () => {
    await expect(createFoo({ name: '' })).rejects.toThrow('name is required');
  });
});
```

### Handler Test Pattern

Test handlers by constructing mock `APIGatewayProxyEvent` objects:

```typescript
import { handler } from '../../../src/presentation/handlers/createFoo';
import { APIGatewayProxyEvent } from 'aws-lambda';

const mockEvent = (body: unknown): Partial<APIGatewayProxyEvent> => ({
  body: JSON.stringify(body),
  headers: {},
  httpMethod: 'POST',
  path: '/foos',
});

it('returns 201 on valid input', async () => {
  const result = await handler(mockEvent({ name: 'Test' }) as APIGatewayProxyEvent, {} as any, () => {});
  expect(result?.statusCode).toBe(201);
});
```

