## TypeScript Standards

- Use `strict: true` in `tsconfig.json`
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow types
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and primitives
- All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed
- Use `as const` for literal types and enums
- Never use non-null assertion (`!`) unless the value is guaranteed by contract; add a comment explaining why

---

## Git Workflow

- Branch naming: `feature/<ticket-id>-short-description`, `fix/<ticket-id>-short-description`
- Commit message format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>` (Conventional Commits)
  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`
  - Example: `feat(contacts): add POST /contacts handler`
- One feature per branch, small focused commits
- Always update `openspec/specs/api-spec.yml` when endpoints change
- Always update `openspec/specs/data-model.md` when DynamoDB schema changes
